-a , --auto <number>
Conditionally change stereo to mono, and/or divide sample rate by two.
The argument is the sum of 1 (change to mono) and 2 (divide sample rate).
It changes stereo to mono only if the channels are identical.
Edway computes the correlation coefficient between channels,
and their average loudnesses. Files with coefficients below 0.98,
with comparable loudnesses, remain stereo, others become mono.
If correlation is higher and loudnesses are comparable,
mono samples are averaged from the two channels,
otherwise the dominant channel becomes the mono signal,
and the weak channel is ignored. It divides sample rate by two only if it
equals or exceeds 32000 samples per second.
This cutoff rate and the channel parameters can be configured in edway.cfg.
